# opendys is 100% client-side by DEFAULT — no backend, no secrets required.
# Vite only exposes variables prefixed with VITE_ to the client bundle.
# Reserved for future build-time toggles:
# VITE_APP_TITLE=opendys

# ── Optional: Enhanced Thai OCR (Cloud) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# opendys can OPTIONALLY use the Typhoon OCR cloud API (https://opentyphoon.ai) for higher-accuracy
# Thai on hard document photos. It is OFF by default and, when enabled, sends that image to Typhoon's
# servers. The key is injected SERVER-SIDE (nginx in prod / the Vite dev proxy) — it is NEVER shipped to
# the browser, so it deliberately does NOT use the VITE_ prefix. Get a free key at https://opentyphoon.ai/
# then uncomment and set:
# TYPHOON_API=your-typhoon-api-key

# ── Optional: IPv6-only egress hosts (advanced) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# nginx resolves the Typhoon upstream (api.opentyphoon.ai) using these resolver flags. The default
# "ipv6=off" preserves IPv4-only resolution and suits IPv4 / dual-stack hosts. If this container runs
# on a host with ONLY IPv6 egress (e.g. an EC2 instance with no public IPv4 that reaches Typhoon over
# IPv6), set "ipv4=off ipv6=on" so nginx resolves the AAAA record instead of stalling on IPv4:
# NGINX_RESOLVER_FLAGS=ipv4=off ipv6=on
